<font face="Arial, Helvetica, verdana, Variable Width"><font size=-1>"</font><b><a href="http://thinkprogress.org/2009/01/26/poll-bush-war-crimes/">1
in 4 Americans believe the Bush administration committed war crimes.</a></b><font size=-1>"
... "In a new telephone survey, Rasmussen Reports has found that <a href="http://www.rasmussenreports.com/public_content/politics/general_politics2/44_of_democrats_say_bush_team_guilty_of_war_crimes">25
percent of voters</a> believe [Republican] President Bush and senior members
of his administration are guilty of war crimes. Forty-four percent of
Democrats and 21 percent of unaffiliated voters believe that war crimes
were committed while just 4 percent of Republicans believe the same." -</font><font size=-2>By
<a href="http://thinkprogress.org/author/Matt">Matt
Corley</a></font></font><font size=-2> -<a href="http://ThinkProgress.org">ThinkProgress.org</a></font>
<hr SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></td>
</tr>
</table></center>

